Principles of voice production, with practice in effective vocal use of American English. Emphasizes student participation. Offered by Communication. Limited to three attempts.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

COMM 230: Case Studies in Persuasion. 3 credits.
Examines common persuasive message strategies and approaches. Covers basic principles of persuasive process. Case studies include advertisements, speeches, and persuasive activities from all segments of society. Offered by Communication. Limited to three attempts.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Undergraduate Regular scale.

