COMM 820: Health Communication Campaigns. 3 credits.
Explores use of communication campaigns to promote health and reduce health risks; examines how health communication campaigns are designed, implemented, and evaluated; and describes the role of communication research throughout the campaign process. Offered by Communication. May not be repeated for credit.
Registration Restrictions: Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Graduate Regular scale.

